      "firm_id": "sybil_16",
      "description": "Up for sale is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) powered by the 3.6L M96 water-cooled flat-six, featuring VarioCam Plus timing for an optimized power band. This driver-spec example features the desirable 6-speed G96 manual transaxle and a factory-optioned limited-slip differential. Mechanical highlights include a dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit, a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS), and a replaced water pump with a composite impeller to ensure cooling system longevity. The suspension geometry is dialed in with Bilstein B6 dampers and refreshed control arm bushings, providing exceptional turn-in and communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc Brembo calipers over cross-drilled rotors. While the exterior displays minor patina from high-speed touring, the drivetrain is robust, leak-free, and pulls hard to the 7,200 RPM redline.",
